channel.title: ElfCity by JaGeX for the N64
channel.description:
JaGeX sure shit out a quality update this time around. The ElfCity's textures make the Sega Genesis cry.
For example: [spoiler][img]http://i.imgur.com/OMewNJR.png[/img][/spoiler]
Jesus christ, does look like an n64 character from Zelda OOT? Is that a face texture!?!
Older areas like the fishing guild look better than this garbage.
Fishing Guild bank: [spoiler][img]http://i.imgur.com/g9oiT49.png[/img][/spoiler]
Like holy fudge.. What the fudge were they thinking?

item.title: ElfCity by JaGeX for the N64
item.dc:creator: @3lv3n_snip3r 3lv3n snip3r
item.description:
@3lv3n_snip3r wrote:

I spent 3 days straight there mining Seren stones. Averaged 1.5m mining xp/day getting 95-99, with the max being 1.75m xp on the second day lol. It’s an amazing skilling place, and the scenery is pretty nice too. The textures aren’t bad unless you zoom up super close on them.

item.title: ElfCity by JaGeX for the N64
item.dc:creator: @HcoJustin HcoJustin
item.description:
@HcoJustin wrote:

Several hours later and quest is done. I don’t see face textures, I do see textured noses and eyes though.

Downloadable Client:
http://i.imgur.com/tIB66RO.jpg
http://i.imgur.com/4rjYsQM.jpg
http://i.imgur.com/mZKbJWm.jpg

HTML5 Client:
http://i.imgur.com/K6Pv452.jpg
http://i.imgur.com/2GSN0q4.jpg
http://i.imgur.com/hNGdI2u.jpg

HTML5 has a much nicer lighting engine, but the DL client has the better ground textures. Taken in OpenGL to best match WebGL
